value.title: Trump and allies pitch yet another woeful voter-fraud theory in Nevada
value.excerpt: Officials have moved to re-do a race in Clark County. It's not the voter fraud smoking gun Trump and his allies suggest.

value.title: Latino voters who fled dictatorships demand four more years for Trump
value.excerpt: Many Latino Trump supporters who escaped authoritarian regimes fear they are once again witnessing widespread election fraud despite lack of evidence.

value.title: Trump asked for options for attacking Iran last week, but held off: source
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump, with two months left in office, last week asked for options on attacking Iran's main nuclear site, but ultimately decided against taking the dramatic step, a U.S. official said on Monday.

value.title: Trump Counts Crowd’s Size Using ‘MAGA Math,’ Says Stephen Colbert
value.excerpt: Ten thousand, a million — it’s just how they count,” Colbert said of Saturday’s Million MAGA March. “You round up for marches, you round down for Covid deaths.”

value.title: 'This isn't a game': Michelle Obama rips into Trump for refusing to concede and says he put her family in danger with 'racist lies'
value.excerpt: The former first lady emphasized the need for a peaceful transfer of power, writing "our democracy is so much bigger than anybody's ego."

value.title: Katy Perry, George Conway jump in to support Trump critic Claudia Conway's 'American Idol' audition
value.excerpt: American Idol' judge Katy Perry welcomed Kellyanne Conway's daughter Claudia, who is auditioning. "Let the games begin," said Perry.

value.title: Trump to reduce troop levels in Afghanistan and Iraq by mid-January
value.excerpt: The Pentagon is expecting orders by the end of this week to reduce troop levels to 2,500 in Afghanistan and in Iraq by mid-January, according to two U.S. officials.

value.title: In new memoir, Obama confronts the ‘racial anxiety’ of Trump supporters
value.excerpt: President Obama has in the past subtly drawn attention to the racial resentment his successor peddles. One notable example was Obama appearing to endorse a Post op-ed written by his former Black staffers criticizing Trump for telling Black American lawmakers critical of his administration to “go back” to wherever they came from.

value.title: 'He's in vengeance mode': Intelligence veterans sound the alarm over Trump's post-election 'bloodlust' and 'decapitation strike' at the Pentagon
value.excerpt: "Trump seems to wake up every day with a kind of anxiety or hatred," said one former official. "He didn't get reelected, so he's in vengeance mode."

value.title: Obama said he was surprised at top Republicans who did a 'complete 180 on everything they claimed to believe' to align with Trump
value.excerpt: Obama told The Atlantic he was not shocked by Trump's "character and behavior" while in office, but at top Republicans who emerged as his allies.

value.title: Trump campaign jettisons major parts of its legal challenge against Pennsylvania’s election results
value.excerpt: The campaign removed an allegation that more than 600,000 votes should be invalidated, capitulating on one of its most aggressive legal claims.

value.title: AP FACT CHECK: Trump wrong on Georgia voter signature checks
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump wrongly claimed on Twitter that Georgia election officials are prevented from verifying signatures on absentee ballot envelopes because of a legal settlement

value.title: Trump Allies Explored Buyout of Newsmax TV as Fox News Alternative
value.excerpt: Hicks Equity Partners, a private-equity firm with ties to a co-chair of the Republican National Committee, has held talks in recent months about acquiring and investing in Newsmax, a fledgling pro-Trump cable channel.

value.title: Spurred on by false claims of fraud, Trump supporters rally in Washington
value.excerpt: Tens of thousands of President Donald Trump's supporters marched through downtown Washington on Saturday, echoing his unsubstantiated claims of election fraud and cheering as his motorcade drove past.

value.title: Trump election lawsuit in Arizona's Maricopa County dismissed, outcome wouldn't have affected races
value.excerpt: By Friday morning, the Trump team had filed a motion acknowledging the outcome of the lawsuit would have no impact on Arizona’s presidential results

value.title: Philadelphia suburbs return with a vengeance to oust Trump
value.excerpt: Voters in Philadelphia’s suburbs hurled perhaps their biggest rebuke yet this month to President Donald Trump and the Republican Party overall

value.title: Rudy Giuliani is reportedly taking charge in Trump's election legal battles — and Twitter is having a field day with it
value.excerpt: "Rudy will soon be appealing all of these adverse rulings to the Supreme Courtyard by Marriott," one person tweeted.

value.title: Donald Trump wins North Carolina
value.excerpt: Donald Trump wins North Carolina. Trump taps Giuliani to take over election legal fight: Sources 24/7 coverage of breaking news and live events

value.title: Trump's Pentagon shake-up has the military worried about its future
value.excerpt: In recent days, President Donald Trump has shaken up Pentagon leadership, firing his defense secretary and installing officials seen as loyalists.

value.title: The Technology 202: Trump will face new rules on Facebook and Twitter after he leaves office
value.excerpt: The president will no longer have special protections afforded to elected officials. But a 2024 run could change that.

value.title: Sheldon Adelson’s Las Vegas Review-Journal Tells Trump To Stop Delaying ‘The Inevitable’
value.excerpt: The billionaire casino tycoon was one of Trump’s biggest donors ahead of the presidential election. Now the newspaper he owns is saying that Trump should concede.

value.title: Far-right protesters, counterdemonstrators plan to gather Saturday in D.C. amid pro-Trump rallies
value.excerpt: The events have been promoted by far-right media personalities, white nationalists and conspiracists — several of whom announced plans to attend. Counterdemonstrations organized by anti-fascist and anti-racism groups are being planned nearby.

value.title: John McCain's widow says it's time for Trump to 'accept the results and get on with the healing'
value.excerpt: Cindy McCain described Joe Biden as "a man of honor" who would "heal the wounds caused by the outgoing administration."

value.title: How long can Republicans keep helping Trump delegitimize the election?
value.excerpt: There are some cracks starting to show – but strong political reasons for Republicans to hang on until Georgia Senate runoffs in January

value.title: Donald Trump supporters can get free food at Kentucky restaurants owned by the same couple. But there's a catch.
value.excerpt: Louisville restaurant owners Troy King and Selena Johnson are offering free food to anyone who trades in Donald Trump merchandise.

value.title: Trump endorses Ronna McDaniel to remain RNC chair
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday endorsed Republican National Commmittee chair Ronna McDaniel to stay on in her position, crediting her with much of the support Trump received in the presidential election that he lost but is contesting.

value.title: Parler, MeWe, Gab gain momentum as conservative social media alternatives in post-Trump age
value.excerpt: The rise of conservative-friendly platform Parler raises the specter of further political polarization through digital means.

value.title: Fox News cuts away from Trump campaign news conference: 'Can't in good countenance continue showing this'
value.excerpt: Fox News anchor Neil Cavuto broke in and cut away from the news conference after "explosive charges" were made about voter fraud without evidence.

value.title: Jimmy Kimmel: Trump Is a Reality Show Host Who Can’t Accept Reality
value.excerpt: Republicans are handling the president with kid gloves because those are the only gloves that fit him,” Kimmel joked of President Trump’s refusal to concede to Joe Biden.

value.title: Why a Trump Loss May Be No Match for Rupert Murdoch’s Realpolitik
value.excerpt: Fox News has lasted through “multiple presidents, and they’re going to be around for multiple more,” said one right-wing media executive.
